Forbes: “Don’t Trust Artificial Intelligence? Time To Open The AI ‘Black Box'” (Sameer Singh quoted)
September 17, 2018 “The more accurate the algorithm, the harder it is to interpret, especially with deep learning,” points out Sameer Singh, assistant professor of computer science at the University of California Irvine. “Computers are increasingly a more important part of our lives, and automation is just going to improve over time, so it’s increasingly important to know why these complicated AI and ML systems are making the decisions that they are.”
Read the full story at Forbes.
